<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06137199 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06137199 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  The shining white Navy hospital ship Mercy, which last month returned from thePersian Gulf war, will be open for public tours from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. as partof the annual Maritime Day celebration Saturday in Oakland's Jack LondonSquare. The 894-foot floating hospital, with 12 operating rooms and 1,000beds, is the nation's largest trauma center afloat or ashore.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MERCY OPENS TO PUBLIC FOR MARITIME DAY  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910516  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  May  </MONTH><PG.COL>  10B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  67  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday May 16, 199100137199,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>